NAME
       tldr - tealdeer, A fast TLDR client

SYNOPSIS
       tldr [OPTION] [COMMAND]...

DESCRIPTION
       tldr is a fast, modern client for the `tldr` project.

OPTIONS
       -h, --help
           Show help message and exit.

       -v, --version
           Show version information.

       -l, --list
           List all available commands in the cache.

       -f, --render
           Render a specific markdown file. Takes a file path as argument.

       -p, --platform PLATFORM
           Override the platform for which the command is rendered.
           Valid options: linux, macos, sunos, windows, android, freebsd,
           netbsd, openbsd.

       -L, --language LANGUAGE
           Override the language used for the command documentation.

       -u, --update
           Update the local cache of command pages.

       --no-auto-update
           If auto-update is configured, disable it for this run.

       -c, --clear-cache
           Clear the local cache of command pages.

       --pager
           Use a pager to page through the output.

       -r, --raw
           Display the raw markdown content instead of rendering it.

       -q, --quiet
           Suppress informational messages.

       --show-paths
           Show file and directory paths used by tldr.

       --seed-config
           Create a basic configuration file for tldr.

       --color WHEN
           Control when to use color in the output.
           Valid options: always, auto, never.

COMMANDS
       <COMMAND>
           Display usage information for the specified command.
           If no command is specified, tldr will show the general help.

FILES
       The following files and directories are used by tldr:

       $CONFIG_DIR/tealdeer
           Default configuration directory for Tealdeer.
           (Typically defaults to ~/.config/tealdeer/)

       $CONFIG_DIR/tealdeer/config.toml
           Default configuration file for Tealdeer. This file contains
           user-defined settings options.

       $CACHE_DIR/tealdeer
           Default cache directory for Tealdeer.
           (Typically defaults to ~/.cache/tealdeer/)

       $CACHE_DIR/tealdeer/tldr-pages
           Default directory where Tealdeer stores cached tldr pages.
           This is automatically updated when running `tldr --update`.

       $DATA_DIR/tealdeer/pages
           Directory for custom tldr pages. These are user-provided
           pages stored separately from the default cache.
           (Typically defaults to ~/.local/share/tealdeer/pages/)

       Note:
           The `$CONFIG_DIR`, `$CACHE_DIR`, and `$DATA_DIR` environment
           variables follow the XDG Base Directory Specification. If
           these are not set, the default locations are used:

           - $HOME/.config for $CONFIG_DIR
           - $HOME/.cache for $CACHE_DIR
           - $HOME/.local/share for $DATA_DIR

EXAMPLES
       tldr tar
           Show usage information for the `tar` command

       tldr -v
           Show the version of tldr.

       tldr -l
           List all commands in the cache.

       tldr -p linux tar
           Show usage information for the `tar` command, rendered for the Linux
           platform.

       tldr -f ~/path/to/file.md
           Render the specified markdown file.

       tldr -u
           Update the local cache of command pages.

       tldr --color auto
           Enable color output based on terminal settings.

